What you need to know:

While spraying tomatoes, one should ensure minimal crop disturbance to avoid interfering with fruit development.Spraying is done after scouting for pests and diseases, guided by records maintained as discussed in our previous article.During flowering and fruit development, tomatoes require high potassium, as this helps in fruit development.During fruiting and flowering, have a regular watering regime to avoid causing stress to the plants. In our next article, we shall focus on the management of pests such as white flies and thrips.